description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Royal Brompton and Harefield NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Royal Brompton Hospital &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Locum Consultant in Adult and Paediatric Cardiothoracic Anaesthesia&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reference: 312-RBH-LCON-ANAE-0009&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Royal Brompton &amp; Harefield NHS Foundation Trust is renowned nationally and internationally for excellence in diagnosis, treatment and research of patients with cardiothoracic diseases. It is the largest postgraduate specialist heart and lung centre in the United Kingdom with sites in Chelsea, London and Harefield, Middlesex. We strive to develop our staff both personally and professionally to ensure our patients get the first-class service they deserve.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Brompton &amp; Harefield NHS Foundation Trust is seeking to appoint a full-time Consultant in Adult and Paediatric Cardiothoracic Anaesthesia. The post is a replacement post. The post is for 6 months, but may be extended by mutual agreement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This clinical role is divided between attending theatre and catheter laboratories, and peri-operative assessment and care as part of the team based approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide clinical services in Anaesthesia in accordance with clinical and legal requirements and in keeping with the international role of the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder is also expected to contribute to the adult and or paediatric on call rota after orientation and dependent upon previous experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are required to be fully registered Medical Practitioners and must be on the GMC’s Specialist Register and should have specialist registration in Anaesthesia, or be within six months of award of CCT by date of interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, please contact Dr Arshad Ghori, Director of Anaesthesia or Dr Kathryn Fogg, Deputy Clinical Lead, Anaesthesia via Secrectary Lindsay Price L.Price@rbht.nhs.uk or on 020 7351 8121. Alternatively, please contact Sophia White, Medical Recruitment Team on 0207 351 8688 or email (s.white3@bht.nhs.uk).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please apply for the position using the &quot;Apply for this job&quot; button. Please complete the online application form and include the full names, work addresses and fax numbers of three clinical referees, one of which must be your current or most recent employer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shortlisting details and interview arrangements will be communicated via email therefore please ensure you check your email account regularly following the closing date. In addition the Trust will be chasing up references via email so please ensure you include the email addresses and contact numbers for your referees to avoid delay in the recruitment process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: Tuesday 24th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: TBC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
